  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba9f; \u0b95\u0bc2\u0bb1\u0bbf 9 \u0b86\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 ; \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If a crime is committed, the situation will worsen; Request to ban demonstrations on 9th; The court refused",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Today (7) the court rejected the request made to issue an order banning the protesting and entering the area near the Presidential Palace in Fort Colombo tomorrow (08) and the day after tomorrow (09).",
        "Colombo Additional Magistrate Keminda Perera rejected the request made by the Fort Police to file a case B 22502/22 under Chapter 414 of Chapter XXXVI of the Penal Code, citing intelligence information.",
        "When this case came up for hearing at the Colombo Additional Magistrate's Court this afternoon (7), a team led by Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bandara appeared on behalf of Fort Police along with Assistant Superintendent of Police Dilruk on behalf of the Attorney General.",
        "Regarding the rights of the demonstrators, a group of lawyers including Nuvan Boppake, Gunaratna Vanni Nayake, Jayantha Dehi Attake, led by President's Counsel Saliya Peiris, appeared.",
        "In the midst of the country's economic crisis, it has been pointed out in an affidavit to the court on behalf of the Fort Police that the economic mystery is located near the Fort President's House.",
        "Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bhandara, who appeared in the court for the police, said that in the context of many star hotels being located in the area, according to the information of the intelligence department, if any crimes are committed during the demonstrations, the foreign tourists staying in the star hotels may leave the country and it will push the crisis-ridden economy further into the abyss. Therefore, he demanded that those involved in the protest should be banned from entering the area where the Presidential Palace is located.",
        "However, the team led by the President's lawyer Saliya Peiris, who was present in the forum, demanded that the request be rejected. They argued that the rights to freedom of speech, expression and peaceful assembly were constitutionally guaranteed.",
        "Justice Keminda Perera, who examined the issues of both sides, said that it is certain that the economic situation will be further affected if crimes are committed in the middle of the protest.",
        "However, the judge also announced the rejection of the police's request to ban the constitutionally guaranteed right.",
        "Police have powers to take action in case of crime. There are ample guidelines in 'Janakosha', Vijitha Perera case judgments (Supreme Court) regarding freedom of expression. The general public has the right to visit any place.",
        "Even now most foreigners have left the country due to fuel and electricity problems.",
        "Hence judicial intervention in this matter is not necessary. Police have powers to take action in case of crime.",
        "So I reject the request of the police.' Justice Keminda Perera said in his order."
      ],
